# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat: A new feature
# * fix: A bug fix
# * docs: Documentation only changes
# * style: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
# * refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# * perf: A code change that improves performance
# * test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# * build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
# * ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
# * chore: Other changes that don't modify src or test files
# * revert: Reverts a previous commit

# Scope should be one of the following for this project:
# * electron: Electron main process, preload scripts
# * react: React frontend application
# * api-utils: Shared types and IPC utilities
# * workspace: Monorepo/workspace configuration
# * docs: Documentation changes

# Subject line should:
# * Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
# * Not capitalize first letter
# * Not end with a period
# * Be no more than 50 characters

# Body should:
# * Use imperative mood
# * Include motivation for the change
# * Contrast with previous behavior

# Footer should:
# * Reference issues and pull requests
# * Include breaking change notes
# * Use "BREAKING CHANGE:" for breaking changes

# Examples:
# feat(react): add audio waveform visualization component
# fix(electron): resolve IPC communication timeout issue
# docs(readme): update installation instructions for pnpm
# refactor(api-utils): simplify type definitions for audio processing
